to eat, your favorite flowers.

00:45:30.126 --> 00:45:32.219
l know everything.

00:45:33.796 --> 00:45:36.424
l also know something else.

00:45:37.533 --> 00:45:42.368
You resent the fact
that Nikhil lends me money.

00:45:44.040 --> 00:45:46.474
So you really aren't a stranger to me.

00:45:46.976 --> 00:45:50.207
But l never imagined...

00:45:51.380 --> 00:45:55.840
l'd one day find myself
sitting by your side.

00:45:56.786 --> 00:46:00.187
-- Did you go to Rangpur?
-- Yes, l did.

00:46:00.289 --> 00:46:03.122
-- How was the trip?
-- Great.

00:46:03.559 --> 00:46:06.960
That's why the first thing l wanted
to see this morning was you.

00:46:08.364 --> 00:46:10.525
Don't you have to leave again?

00:46:10.633 --> 00:46:12.999
-- Where to?
-- To Rangpur.

00:46:13.102 --> 00:46:15.900
lsn't that your base?

00:46:16.605 --> 00:46:20.598
That was the idea, but not anymore.

00:46:21.143 --> 00:46:22.735
lt's not?

00:46:25.247 --> 00:46:27.181
Let me be frank with you.

00:46:27.716 --> 00:46:29.911
l want to be near you when l work.

00:46:34.490 --> 00:46:37.789
Just like a bee working for the queen.

00:46:37.893 --> 00:46:39.451
You'll be the queen bee.

00:46:42.598 --> 00:46:44.463
Do you have any objection?

00:46:45.801 --> 00:46:49.669
But won't you find it inconvenient
working from here?

00:46:55.778 --> 00:46:57.405
That's true.

00:47:00.249 --> 00:47:05.949
l don't think Nikhil will approve of this.

00:47:10.025 --> 00:47:11.720
But the thing is...

00:47:14.864 --> 00:47:17.094
l am essentially...

00:47:20.503 --> 00:47:22.334
a stubborn man.

00:47:24.173 --> 00:47:27.609
l just can't accept Nikhil's attitude.

00:47:29.379 --> 00:47:35.511
l want to promote
the Swadeshi cause right here...

00:47:36.720 --> 00:47:38.745
and l need your help.

00:47:40.490 --> 00:47:43.391
But l really know nothing about your work.

00:47:43.493 --> 00:47:47.224
l know that you
give speeches. ls that all?

00:47:49.633 --> 00:47:52.431
That's one of the most important things.

00:47:53.370 --> 00:47:55.736
Persuasion can work wonders.

00:47:57.507 --> 00:47:59.031
Wait.

00:48:00.343 --> 00:48:02.868
lf you really want to know about our work,

00:48:03.613 --> 00:48:05.080
then read this.

00:48:05.182 --> 00:48:06.444
OUR STRUGGLE

00:48:06.550 --> 00:48:09.144
lt contains everything you need to know.

00:48:13.957 --> 00:48:15.788
l will definitely read it.

00:48:17.727 --> 00:48:20.161
May l tell you something now?

00:48:21.364 --> 00:48:24.492
One of the biggest markets
in this area is here, in Sukhsayar.

00:48:24.601 --> 00:48:27.764
Did you know that?
-- So l've heard.

00:48:28.338 --> 00:48:34.140
lt's the only market in the area
where foreign goods are still being sold.

00:48:34.411 --> 00:48:38.245
Elsewhere, the landowners
have prohibited their sale,

00:48:38.348 --> 00:48:39.940
but Nikhil hasn't.

00:48:41.051 --> 00:48:43.645
l'm going to do my best to change that,

00:48:44.020 --> 00:48:48.753
but, with your help,
my task will be much easier.

00:48:48.858 --> 00:48:52.385
l'm afraid you're overestimating
my capabilities.

00:48:52.495 --> 00:48:54.360
Not at all.

00:48:55.165 --> 00:48:59.465
Nikhil may be my friend,
but he's your husband.

00:48:59.569 --> 00:49:02.538
You have much more influence
over him than l do.

00:49:02.639 --> 00:49:06.405
My husband isn't easily swayed.

00:49:06.710 --> 00:49:08.302
l know...

00:49:09.045 --> 00:49:11.878
but l think he'll listen to you.

00:49:16.586 --> 00:49:19.248
l know how much you mean to Nikhil.

00:49:20.624 --> 00:49:23.092
Will you try just once to persuade him?

00:49:25.695 --> 00:49:28.960
Nikhil's tenants wouldn't dare
to go against his will.

00:49:29.065 --> 00:49:32.296
He only has to tell them not to bring
any more foreign goods to the market.

00:49:33.470 --> 00:49:35.267
And if l fail to persuade him?

00:49:36.072 --> 00:49:38.768
l'll be happy if you just try.

00:49:40.043 --> 00:49:42.136
lf you fail, l'll find another way.

00:49:43.046 --> 00:49:45.037
Not without the queen bee's
knowledge, of course.

00:49:46.583 --> 00:49:49.177
Can l depend on you?

00:49:50.253 --> 00:49:51.811
l'll try my best.

00:49:59.663 --> 00:50:01.324
The more l see you,

00:50:02.032 --> 00:50:04.057
the more l admire you.

00:50:16.079 --> 00:50:17.478
l think l'll --

00:50:18.014 --> 00:50:20.312
Okay, you may go now.

00:50:24.521 --> 00:50:26.318
Oh, and one more thing.

00:50:28.291 --> 00:50:29.519
This item of yours.

00:50:37.200 --> 00:50:42.536
This is the only foreign item
l will keep with me.

00:50:47.310 --> 00:50:49.744
Did you see Sandip today?

00:50:50.980 --> 00:50:52.277
<i>Yes.</i>

00:50:54.984 --> 00:50:56.781
How is he doing?

00:50:58.254 --> 00:51:00.188
He's worried.

00:51:00.290 --> 00:51:01.780
Why?

00:51:03.460 --> 00:51:05.758
You won't let him promote
the Swadeshi cause here.

00:51:06.196 --> 00:51:09.597
Nonsense.
You heard me yourself.

00:51:09.966 --> 00:51:14.062
He's free to fight for his cause
as long as he leaves my estate alone.

00:51:15.572 --> 00:51:17.938
He says he's staying here.

00:51:19.242 --> 00:51:20.800
Staying here?

00:51:21.778 --> 00:51:23.268
That's what he says.

00:51:24.080 --> 00:51:26.241
He's going to stay and work here.

00:51:28.651 --> 00:51:30.676
That wouldn't be right.

00:51:31.921 --> 00:51:33.889
But all of Bengal has taken up
the Swadeshi cause.

00:51:33.990 --> 00:51:35.082
Why don't you?

00:51:36.126 --> 00:51:41.496
That would mean banning
all foreign goods from the market.

00:51:42.432 --> 00:51:45.230
Harish Kundu can do that, but not me.

00:51:46.069 --> 00:51:48.299
Surely the market belongs to you.
Why can't you?

00:51:49.305 --> 00:51:51.296
lt's not my market, Bimala.

00:51:51.808 --> 00:51:55.073
The market belongs to the traders
who sell their goods there.

00:51:55.178 --> 00:51:56.839
They're poor.

00:51:58.448 --> 00:52:03.317
Foreign goods are cheaper
and of better quality than lndian goods.

00:52:05.388 --> 00:52:09.415
The poor villagers can afford them.
How can l force them not to buy them?

00:52:12.395 --> 00:52:16.559
Swadeshi is for those who can afford it,

00:52:16.666 --> 00:52:18.497
not for the poor.

00:52:23.473 --> 00:52:25.202
What are you thinking?

00:52:26.075 --> 00:52:27.975
Can we follow Swadeshi...

00:52:30.480 --> 00:52:32.209
without making the poor suffer?

00:52:32.315 --> 00:52:34.010
ls it possible?

00:52:34.684 --> 00:52:38.120
lf it were possible,
l'd definitely support Swadeshi.

00:52:39.255 --> 00:52:41.689
You believe the very idea
of Swadeshi is wrong.

00:52:43.092 --> 00:52:45.754
Even if l do,
who would listen to me?

00:52:45.862 --> 00:52:48.296
The entire country supports Swadeshi.

00:52:49.098 --> 00:52:51.589
You yourself believe Sandip is right.

00:52:51.701 --> 00:52:53.931
Many others must feel the same way.

00:52:55.839 --> 00:53:02.677
But l believe that coercing the poor
can only harm our country.

00:53:08.551 --> 00:53:10.951
l can see you're not convinced.

00:53:12.055 --> 00:53:14.683
l was looking at it differently.

00:53:14.791 --> 00:53:18.386
l was thinking that
something has to be done.

00:53:18.495 --> 00:53:20.520
Even if it means
hardship for the poor now,

00:53:20.630 --> 00:53:22.825
it will help them in the long run.

00:53:23.233 --> 00:53:26.202
The Swadeshi care about this country.

00:53:27.770 --> 00:53:34.073
l believe what they care about
is an abstract idea of this country,

00:53:34.177 --> 00:53:36.771
this country as the Mother Goddess.

00:53:37.580 --> 00:53:39.377
The nation is our mother.

00:53:39.482 --> 00:53:44.715
Worship our mother,
work for our mother, pray to our mother.

00:53:45.488 --> 00:53:48.321
Everything you do is for our mother.

00:53:48.992 --> 00:53:51.426
Heal our mother's pain.

00:53:52.161 --> 00:53:53.822
l can understand that.

00:53:54.664 --> 00:53:57.462
And l can understand why
that idea appeals to women.

00:53:58.101 --> 00:54:00.934
l know how you feel, Bimala,

00:54:01.037 --> 00:54:03.403
but l don't feel the same way.

00:54:27.463 --> 00:54:29.624
Those things you said tonight...

00:54:29.966 --> 00:54:32.127
Were those your own thoughts?

00:54:32.235 --> 00:54:34.396
Why are you asking me this?

00:54:36.573 --> 00:54:39.599
l felt as if you were speaking for Sandip.

00:54:39.709 --> 00:54:42.610
Sandip is your friend, not mine.

00:54:44.213 --> 00:54:49.412
l thought you two had teamed up
''in right earnest'' to fight for a higher cause.

00:54:50.320 --> 00:54:53.687
He's working on the public front,
and you on the domestic.

00:54:53.790 --> 00:54:55.348
What an idea!

00:55:03.600 --> 00:55:05.761
Will you have daily meetings?

00:55:06.302 --> 00:55:11.171
You insisted that l meet your friend,
so you can spare me the insinuations.

00:55:24.621 --> 00:55:27.249
l just asked a simple question.

00:55:28.024 --> 00:55:30.584
l wasn't insinuating anything.
-- Very well.

00:55:30.693 --> 00:55:33.719
lf it upsets you so much,
l won't go outside anymore.

00:55:34.631 --> 00:55:36.565
You're mistaken, Bimala.

00:55:36.666 --> 00:55:38.930
l'm not upset at all.

00:55:39.435 --> 00:55:42.598
After all, l know you both so well.

00:55:42.705 --> 00:55:47.165
Why shouldn't you go outside?
-- Because l don't want to.

00:55:48.277 --> 00:55:49.869
You're being unreasonable.

00:55:49.979 --> 00:55:53.540
l've been out twice already.
l don't have to go out every day.

00:55:56.285 --> 00:55:58.014
Very well.

00:56:08.031 --> 00:56:13.298
l won't restrict you
from going where you please.

00:56:14.570 --> 00:56:19.371
As l told you,
you are completely free.

00:56:20.510 --> 00:56:24.947
But l must tell you one thing.

00:56:26.816 --> 00:56:30.843
lf you tell me you want to give up
wearing foreign clothes,

00:56:31.454 --> 00:56:36.448
or do without your foreign
perfumes, shoes and soap,

00:56:36.759 --> 00:56:38.989
l won't mind at all.

00:56:39.295 --> 00:56:41.695
But clamping down on poor traders

00:56:43.366 --> 00:56:46.494
by banning foreign goods in the market

00:56:47.437 --> 00:56:50.497
means going against
my own beliefs and principles.

00:56:51.074 --> 00:56:53.372
l could never do that, Bimala.

00:56:59.816 --> 00:57:03.752
Swadeshi is something l can't take lightly.

00:57:10.026 --> 00:57:14.520
<i>The weak say, ''Whatever fate</i>
<i>has given to me is mine. "</i>

00:57:14.630 --> 00:57:18.964
<i>And the impotent agree with them.</i>

00:57:19.068 --> 00:57:21.832
<i>''OnIy what I can snatch away</i>
<i>by force is mine. "</i>

00:57:21.938 --> 00:57:24.463
<i>That is what experience has taught us.</i>

00:57:24.574 --> 00:57:27.737
<i>My country is not mine</i>
<i>simpIy because I was born here.</i>

00:57:27.844 --> 00:57:31.712
<i>It becomes mine</i>
<i>onIy when I am abIe to win it by force.</i>

00:57:31.814 --> 00:57:34.146
<i>OnIy then can the nation be mine.</i>

00:57:39.589 --> 00:57:46.654
This funeral pyre celebrates the cremation
of foreign trade in your village.

00:57:47.463 --> 00:57:49.727
These ashes are sacred.

00:57:50.099 --> 00:57:51.828
Hail Motherland!

00:58:07.316 --> 00:58:12.618
AN URGENT MATTER
REGARDlNG OUR CAUSE

00:58:23.866 --> 00:58:27.768
-- Please give this to Mrs. Choudhury.
-- Very well.

00:59:09.545 --> 00:59:11.604
Madam isn't feeling well, sir.

00:59:16.619 --> 00:59:18.450
l see.

00:59:29.498 --> 00:59:32.626
-- You know the headmaster, don't you?
-- Yes, of course.

00:59:32.735 --> 00:59:35.966
Good morning.
l hope you are doing well.

00:59:37.173 --> 00:59:39.937
Not as long as you're around.

00:59:43.579 --> 00:59:44.876
How come?

00:59:45.281 --> 00:59:48.717
His students have all disappeared
since you arrived.

00:59:50.253 --> 00:59:55.782
But you must admit that working
for one's country helps build character.

00:59:58.494 --> 01:00:02.897
One of my students was influenced
by the Swadeshi movement.

01:00:02.999 --> 01:00:06.901
He threw a stone at Mrs. Choudhury's
governess, Miss Gilby.

01:00:07.503 --> 01:00:10.267
Would you consider that
an example of character building?

01:00:10.806 --> 01:00:14.071
But that happened before l came.

01:00:14.610 --> 01:00:16.908
You can't blame me for that.

01:00:17.013 --> 01:00:20.380
After all, you must admit
that a few such incidents

01:00:20.483 --> 01:00:24.886
are inevitable in times
of great social upheaval.

01:00:25.454 --> 01:00:28.082
You even roped in my best student.

01:00:28.190 --> 01:00:30.283
Who? Amulya?

01:00:32.061 --> 01:00:34.325
He'd have won a scholarship
if he'd taken his exam.

01:00:34.430 --> 01:00:37.160
You stole that opportunity from him.

01:00:37.700 --> 01:00:40.863
Amulya? l didn't rope him in.
He joined of his own accord.

01:00:41.370 --> 01:00:46.034
What about the other rowdy dissolutes
who have joined your team?

01:00:46.142 --> 01:00:49.236
They're the worst troublemakers in the village.

01:00:49.345 --> 01:00:51.870
They're not troublemakers anymore, sir.

01:00:51.981 --> 01:00:54.882
They're fighting for the cause.
They're working hard.

01:00:55.351 --> 01:00:59.219
With two exceptions,
everyone here is working for the cause.

01:00:59.322 --> 01:01:00.983
One of them is you.

01:01:01.857 --> 01:01:05.793
The other one is your former
student Nikhilesh Choudhury.

01:01:05.895 --> 01:01:09.126
l regret that
l couldn't persuade him to join.

01:01:09.231 --> 01:01:11.995
Like you, he turns a deaf ear
to the Swadeshi cause.

01:01:12.101 --> 01:01:15.036
No, he isn't against Swadeshi ideals.

01:01:15.137 --> 01:01:19.267
He's against your
destructive brand of Swadeshi.

01:01:19.875 --> 01:01:22.139
He practiced Swadeshi long before you,

01:01:22.244 --> 01:01:25.213
and he never relied
on any battle cries or mantras.

01:01:25.314 --> 01:01:28.078
-- l know that.
-- You know nothing!

01:01:28.184 --> 01:01:30.277
Do you know about his Swadeshi bank?

01:01:30.386 --> 01:01:33.844
Or his Swadeshi sugar factory,
his soap factory?

01:01:33.956 --> 01:01:39.189
Do you know he set up his own looms
for weaving Swadeshi cloth?

01:01:39.595 --> 01:01:44.498
Where were you
and your ''Hail Motherland'' then?

01:01:45.034 --> 01:01:48.561
Do you know how much
he spent for Swadeshi?

01:01:48.671 --> 01:01:50.696
-- Please, headmaster --
-- You stay out of this!

01:01:50.806 --> 01:01:55.209
These things must be said.
-- But that's what l keep telling him.

01:01:55.311 --> 01:01:58.040
lf both of us have the same goals,
then why doesn't he join us?

01:01:58.048 --> 01:02:01.950
You don't have the same goals.
There are many differences.

01:02:02.052 --> 01:02:06.421
Your goal is power and leadership.

01:02:06.523 --> 01:02:08.684
You don't care about the people!

01:02:08.792 --> 01:02:11.590
Nikhil never thought about himself.

01:02:11.695 --> 01:02:16.428
People are applauding you
and singing your praises.

01:02:17.300 --> 01:02:19.632
Nikhil was ridiculed.

01:02:19.736 --> 01:02:24.366
He had no head for business,
so his brand of Swadeshi didn't last.

01:02:24.474 --> 01:02:26.806
But his way was the right way.

01:02:27.244 --> 01:02:28.836
Yours is wrong.

01:02:28.945 --> 01:02:30.572
lt's more than wrong.

01:02:30.680 --> 01:02:32.739
lt's dangerous.

01:02:35.352 --> 01:02:37.047
Give those to me.

01:02:38.221 --> 01:02:41.054
l'll drop by this evening.

01:02:45.262 --> 01:02:47.162
My goodness.

01:02:50.300 --> 01:02:53.701
Please, Nikhil, l implore you.

01:02:53.804 --> 01:02:56.602
Keep that headmaster away from me.

01:02:56.706 --> 01:03:00.665
l came here to give speeches,
not listen to them.

01:03:02.345 --> 01:03:04.336
Are you planning to stay here and work?

01:03:11.588 --> 01:03:16.082
l'm going to speak
at your market this afternoon.

01:03:17.594 --> 01:03:19.892
That's where our greatest
challenge lies, Nikhil.

01:03:21.364 --> 01:03:26.427
Not where the landowner
is already in favor of Swadeshi,

01:03:28.105 --> 01:03:29.902
but where he isn't.

01:03:30.006 --> 01:03:32.031
But remember, Sandip,

01:03:32.642 --> 01:03:35.440
most of my tenants are poor Muslims.

01:03:37.080 --> 01:03:42.108
l don't want them harassed.

01:03:43.620 --> 01:03:48.284
lf l see that happening,
l will be forced to intervene.

01:03:49.659 --> 01:03:52.753
lf they prove to be obstacles
to our revolution,

01:03:53.029 --> 01:03:55.429
l'll have to take the necessary measures.

01:03:55.899 --> 01:03:57.799
Many Muslims have accepted Swadeshi.

01:03:59.035 --> 01:04:00.900
They were forced to do so.

01:04:02.305 --> 01:04:04.273
lt will happen here too.

01:04:07.744 --> 01:04:09.644
l've said what l had to say.

01:04:10.480 --> 01:04:14.746
What you do now is up to you.

01:04:20.957 --> 01:04:23.187
As you all know,

01:04:23.293 --> 01:04:25.625
our English rulers

01:04:25.729 --> 01:04:29.665
have divided Bengal in two.

01:04:30.100 --> 01:04:37.632
This amounts to erecting a wall
between Hindus and Muslims.

01:04:37.974 --> 01:04:43.469
They have not given us
the right to break this wall,

01:04:43.580 --> 01:04:47.983
but, to foil the government,
we have chosen a different path.

01:04:48.084 --> 01:04:50.712
One important way to fight the partition

01:04:50.820 --> 01:04:56.053
is to stop selling foreign goods
in our markets.

01:04:56.760 --> 01:05:02.460
Salt, sugar, cloth and soap
are all everyday items

01:05:02.566 --> 01:05:05.865
which are only available
as foreign products at your market.

01:05:06.570 --> 01:05:09.004
By selling their foreign goods here,

01:05:09.105 --> 01:05:14.236
the British are making
a lot of money in our country,

01:05:14.344 --> 01:05:19.179
while we keep growing poorer.

01:05:19.282 --> 01:05:21.876
This is wrong.
This must stop.

01:05:21.985 --> 01:05:25.443
We've tolerated this up to now,
but no more.

01:05:26.056 --> 01:05:32.154
l know that lndian substitutes
for foreign goods are not always available,

01:05:32.262 --> 01:05:36.995
so you've had to trade with foreign goods
because that's all you had.

01:05:37.100 --> 01:05:40.467
But if we can all make sacrifices

01:05:40.570 --> 01:05:44.472
and produce our own goods,

01:05:44.574 --> 01:05:48.305
then we will overcome these difficulties.

01:05:48.578 --> 01:05:51.911
Brothers, we are depending on you.

01:05:52.515 --> 01:05:54.449
lf you come forward and join us,

01:05:54.551 --> 01:05:57.418
together we will stop
the partitioning of Bengal

01:05:57.520 --> 01:05:59.988
and regain our pride.

01:06:00.523 --> 01:06:04.983
And now, do you see
this circle here before me?

01:06:05.095 --> 01:06:10.362
Throw all your foreign goods
into the circle of flags.

01:06:11.234 --> 01:06:14.294
lndian substitutes will be made.

01:06:15.138 --> 01:06:18.198
Many manufacturers
have come forward to help us.

01:06:18.642 --> 01:06:21.805
Have no fear of losing your livelihood.

01:06:22.445 --> 01:06:26.108
Today's loss will not be lost forever.

01:06:26.216 --> 01:06:30.983
Now l ask you to throw all
of your foreign goods into the circle.

01:06:31.354 --> 01:06:36.348
The land that gave birth to you,
the land that you love...

01:06:36.459 --> 01:06:38.950
Now is the time to help her.

01:06:39.429 --> 01:06:43.126
Foreign cloth, foreign thread,

01:06:43.233 --> 01:06:46.464
foreign sugar, foreign salt,

01:06:47.037 --> 01:06:48.834
foreign scissors and knives,

01:06:48.938 --> 01:06:52.430
foreign matches,
and everything else foreign...

01:06:52.542 --> 01:06:55.067
Throw them in that circle.

01:06:55.178 --> 01:06:58.807
We beseech you.
Don't just sit there.

01:06:58.915 --> 01:07:01.247
Help the Swadeshi cause.

01:07:01.351 --> 01:07:05.310
We want to hear it from the maharaja!
Let him come here.

01:07:05.822 --> 01:07:07.187
We won't listen to you!

01:07:09.092 --> 01:07:11.617
Your maharaja is my friend.

01:07:11.728 --> 01:07:14.128
l'm his guest.

01:07:14.230 --> 01:07:17.495
lsn't that proof enough
that l have his support?

01:07:17.600 --> 01:07:20.592
We're traders.
lf we have nothing to sell, we'll starve!

01:07:20.704 --> 01:07:23.798
We've tried selling lndian goods.

01:07:23.907 --> 01:07:25.204
Nobody buys them.

01:07:25.308 --> 01:07:28.106
You're a gentleman.
You have money.

01:07:28.211 --> 01:07:31.942
lt's easy for you to say,
''Don't sell foreign goods.''

01:07:32.048 --> 01:07:34.881
We're poor!
How will we survive?

01:07:41.157 --> 01:07:44.126
<i>It's cIear that persuasion</i>
<i>won't work on NikhiI's estate.</i>

01:07:44.227 --> 01:07:46.821
<i>We'II have to use other means.</i>

01:07:47.297 --> 01:07:51.961
<i>Any compromise on foreign goods</i>
<i>wouId crippIe our movement.</i>

01:07:54.037 --> 01:07:57.097
<i>HaiI MotherIand!</i>

01:08:36.012 --> 01:08:37.479
This is Mr. Kulada.

01:08:37.580 --> 01:08:39.275
Greetings.

01:08:39.382 --> 01:08:40.474
Please follow me.

01:08:46.156 --> 01:08:49.091
Were those stolen from the villagers?

01:08:55.932 --> 01:08:57.399
Have a seat.

01:08:58.201 --> 01:09:02.763
You may enjoy your bonfire, but the villagers
will file a complaint against you.

01:09:05.041 --> 01:09:08.477
We'll set fire to their crops if they do.

01:09:09.746 --> 01:09:11.338
Can't we try picketing?

01:09:13.283 --> 01:09:14.875
We can make them understand.

01:09:15.385 --> 01:09:17.376
lt's worked in other places.

01:09:17.921 --> 01:09:20.082
l know what works and what doesn't.

01:09:20.190 --> 01:09:22.385
Picketing won't work in Sukhsayar.

01:09:24.327 --> 01:09:26.158
Please sit, Mr. Kulada.

01:09:33.036 --> 01:09:35.197
A foreign brand, l see.

01:09:35.305 --> 01:09:38.172
Yes, it's the only exception
l make to Swadeshi.

01:09:38.274 --> 01:09:40.936
-- May l have one?
-- Be my guest.

01:09:44.147 --> 01:09:45.842
These people can't be persuaded, Amulya.

01:09:46.282 --> 01:09:48.113
They've been pampered too much.

01:09:48.218 --> 01:09:55.590
Listen, l've been the manager of this estate
since the maharaja's father was alive.

01:09:57.293 --> 01:09:59.784
The father was a tough one.

01:09:59.896 --> 01:10:02.126
The trouble is the son.

01:10:02.232 --> 01:10:04.257
lf only he'd been firm with them,

01:10:04.367 --> 01:10:08.098
he could have brought
these villagers to their knees.

01:10:08.204 --> 01:10:11.037
lt would have been smooth sailing for you.

01:10:13.543 --> 01:10:16.603
Anyway, tell me how you can help us.

01:10:17.981 --> 01:10:21.940
lf you can't stop the influx
of foreign goods,

01:10:22.752 --> 01:10:26.188
you can't stop the trade of foreign goods.

01:10:27.290 --> 01:10:31.317
Those boats bring the goods in.

01:10:32.362 --> 01:10:36.628
-- You'll have to deal with the boatmen first.
-- Can you do that for me?

01:10:37.834 --> 01:10:43.568
The problem is that the boatmen's
leader is very stubborn.

01:10:45.241 --> 01:10:47.232
Who is he?
What's his name?

01:10:47.343 --> 01:10:51.040
Mirjan.
He's a hard nut to crack.

01:10:52.515 --> 01:10:56.212
-- Can he be persuaded?
-- Where there's a will, there's a way.

01:10:57.120 --> 01:11:02.820
A boat which sails
is also a boat which sinks.

01:11:06.362 --> 01:11:10.389
But it's going to take
more than words to do this job.

01:11:11.234 --> 01:11:13.930
lt will take...
-- Money?

01:11:14.537 --> 01:11:16.971
We have to stop tongues from wagging,

01:11:17.073 --> 01:11:20.634
pay compensation,
bribe the police.

01:11:20.743 --> 01:11:22.506
That all takes money.

01:11:25.815 --> 01:11:28.306
lt's not like we don't have any money,

01:11:28.418 --> 01:11:31.876
and more can be raised if necessary.

01:11:31.988 --> 01:11:35.082
Then you can rely on me.

01:11:35.892 --> 01:11:39.919
l'll do the dirty work,

01:11:40.029 --> 01:11:43.556
but if something goes wrong,

01:11:43.666 --> 01:11:45.463
you're on your own.

01:11:48.271 --> 01:11:50.796
You don't need to worry about that.

01:11:50.907 --> 01:11:53.637
Even so, if l get into any sort of trouble,

01:11:53.743 --> 01:11:56.439
l have no intention of taking all the blame.

01:12:04.554 --> 01:12:07.216
l'm keeping this letter you wrote me.

01:12:10.426 --> 01:12:12.485
<i>I didn't go.</i>

01:12:12.595 --> 01:12:14.529
<i>He asked for me.</i>

01:12:14.631 --> 01:12:19.796
<i>I gave an excuse and stayed inside,</i>
<i>but what good did it do?</i>

01:12:19.902 --> 01:12:23.861
<i>I was thinking of him aII day yesterday.</i>

01:12:23.973 --> 01:12:26.703
<i>Why shouId this happen to a woman</i>

01:12:26.809 --> 01:12:33.305
<i>who has never thought about any man</i>
<i>other than her own husband?</i>

01:12:33.750 --> 01:12:36.548
Madam, how do you want
the fish prepared?

01:12:36.653 --> 01:12:38.518
You never told me.

01:12:38.889 --> 01:12:41.084
Make a curry with ground mustard seed.

01:12:49.966 --> 01:12:51.092
<i>Madam?</i>

01:12:53.070 --> 01:12:54.662
Yes, Nanku?

01:12:54.771 --> 01:12:56.966
<i>There's a Ietter for you.</i>

01:13:01.978 --> 01:13:04.970
OUR STRUGGLE

01:13:06.216 --> 01:13:08.150
Are you feeling any better?

01:13:10.087 --> 01:13:10.951
Yes.

01:13:11.721 --> 01:13:15.248
This boy from our group
was very eager to meet you.

01:13:18.929 --> 01:13:21.864
You met me once before when l was little.

01:13:21.965 --> 01:13:23.660
l came with my mother.

01:13:23.767 --> 01:13:26.292
-- What's your mother's name?
-- Soudamini Devi.

01:13:28.105 --> 01:13:32.041
-- Are you Nibaron Ghosal's son?
-- Yes. My name is Amulya.

01:13:33.910 --> 01:13:36.777
-- How old are you?
-- Seventeen.

01:13:36.880 --> 01:13:39.348
l was about to take
my final exam, but l didn't.

01:13:39.950 --> 01:13:42.043
Because of Swadeshi?

01:13:42.152 --> 01:13:44.052
Amulya is very hardworking.

01:13:45.021 --> 01:13:46.989
He remembers the entire <i>Bhagavadgita.</i>

01:13:47.824 --> 01:13:49.621
Really?

01:13:50.527 --> 01:13:51.994
Here it is.

01:13:52.095 --> 01:13:54.996
-- Do you always carry it with you?
-- Always.

01:13:55.098 --> 01:13:58.625
The <i>Bhagavadgita</i> gives one courage
to overcome one's fears.

01:13:58.735 --> 01:14:00.862
Even to die for one's country.

01:14:03.540 --> 01:14:06.008
Aren't you afraid to die?

01:14:06.109 --> 01:14:08.976
''For the soul, there is neither birth
nor death at any time.

01:14:09.079 --> 01:14:12.344
He has not come into being, does not come
into being, and will not come into being.

01:14:12.449 --> 01:14:15.543
He is unborn, eternal,
ever--existing and primeval.

01:14:15.652 --> 01:14:18.678
He is not slain when the body is slain.''

01:14:18.788 --> 01:14:21.120
Even when a man dies,
his soul lives on.

01:14:21.224 --> 01:14:23.692
Okay, Amulya.
You may go now.

01:14:25.762 --> 01:14:28.196
Mr. Sandip said you believe in Swadeshi.

01:14:28.298 --> 01:14:30.664
l wanted to pay my respects.

01:14:30.767 --> 01:14:32.064
l'll take my leave, sister.

01:14:33.036 --> 01:14:35.527
l'll come again.
-- Please do.

01:14:35.639 --> 01:14:36.936
Hail Motherland.

01:14:38.308 --> 01:14:40.538
-- Hail Motherland.
-- Good--bye.

01:14:51.988 --> 01:14:53.683
What are you thinking?

01:14:54.558 --> 01:14:58.358
ls there any danger to your life
in the work you do?

01:15:01.298 --> 01:15:02.788
Well...

01:15:04.601 --> 01:15:08.867
Since we're fighting against
the powerful British government,

01:15:10.807 --> 01:15:12.365
of course there is.

01:15:19.182 --> 01:15:22.208
But my boys are brave.

01:15:23.853 --> 01:15:25.616
My courage doesn't begin to match theirs.

01:15:25.722 --> 01:15:28.316
That's a strange confession from a leader.

01:15:31.595 --> 01:15:33.961
Sometimes the truth comes out.

01:15:39.002 --> 01:15:40.936
Now will you tell me the truth?

01:15:42.505 --> 01:15:43.767
What truth?

01:15:45.108 --> 01:15:47.372
After so many years,

01:15:47.477 --> 01:15:50.207
why did you suddenly decide
to come out of your confinement?

01:15:50.914 --> 01:15:53.144
Don't you know why?

01:15:53.550 --> 01:15:55.415
How would l know?

01:15:55.518 --> 01:15:57.486
You should know.

01:15:58.655 --> 01:16:02.557
You should, but you're a man.

01:16:02.659 --> 01:16:04.650
You don't have a woman's intuition.

01:16:06.596 --> 01:16:07.824
Will you tell me?

01:16:24.814 --> 01:16:26.008
Why?

01:16:35.225 --> 01:16:38.683
l'd never been face--to--face
with a leader before.

01:16:40.830 --> 01:16:44.732
l fear the leader may have let you down.

01:16:52.809 --> 01:16:55.471
Not so far.

01:17:19.369 --> 01:17:20.927
You play the piano too?

01:17:22.505 --> 01:17:24.496
l was taking lessons.

01:17:24.841 --> 01:17:26.206
Piano...

01:17:27.243 --> 01:17:28.835
singing.

01:17:29.746 --> 01:17:31.509
English songs?

01:18:03.847 --> 01:18:05.644
You didn't come yesterday.

01:18:06.249 --> 01:18:11.186
l had a feeling you weren't really ill.

01:18:11.955 --> 01:18:14.685
l racked my brain all day trying to guess...

01:18:15.725 --> 01:18:22.324
what l had done or said to annoy you.

01:18:24.801 --> 01:18:28.293
You still haven't told me
why you called.

01:18:28.938 --> 01:18:31.202
l just wanted to see you.

01:18:32.776 --> 01:18:34.505
ls that the only reason?

01:18:37.580 --> 01:18:39.673
l didn't see you yesterday,

01:18:40.250 --> 01:18:42.377
and it turned out
to be a dismal day for me.

01:18:42.919 --> 01:18:45.251
My pride as a leader...

01:18:46.222 --> 01:18:47.814
was badly shaken.

01:18:48.792 --> 01:18:50.885
The people won't listen to you?

01:18:51.361 --> 01:18:54.694
Sometimes words are not enough.

01:18:54.798 --> 01:18:58.791
-- What do you do then?
-- l try other ways.

01:18:59.469 --> 01:19:00.936
May l know what ways?

01:19:02.505 --> 01:19:04.996
Because my husband's
not going to help you.

01:19:09.412 --> 01:19:10.606
Nikhil said so?

01:19:19.389 --> 01:19:21.653
Do you know what l feel
like doing sometimes?

01:19:22.492 --> 01:19:24.392
To hell with Swadeshi.

01:19:24.961 --> 01:19:27.794
l'll spend my life
chatting with the queen bee.

01:19:29.699 --> 01:19:31.257
With me?

01:19:31.734 --> 01:19:32.701
Chatting?

01:19:33.937 --> 01:19:35.700
Would that bother you?

01:19:39.142 --> 01:19:40.609
Why are you laughing?

01:19:41.177 --> 01:19:43.873
That's so absurd.

01:19:43.980 --> 01:19:48.041
You're not the type to spend
even an hour chatting.

01:19:51.187 --> 01:19:52.654
You're right.

01:19:54.290 --> 01:19:55.689
The truth is...

01:19:56.960 --> 01:19:58.655
l need Swadeshi...

01:20:00.230 --> 01:20:02.130
just as much as l need you.

01:20:04.834 --> 01:20:07.894
l don't want you to stop
fighting for the country.

01:20:09.072 --> 01:20:13.372
My husband and l don't see
eye to eye on that matter.

01:20:13.843 --> 01:20:18.405
He has many virtues,
and l admire him for that.

01:20:19.082 --> 01:20:25.214
But, for a man, he is much too placid.

01:20:25.321 --> 01:20:28.757
A person can't afford to be so placid
at a time like this.

01:20:32.295 --> 01:20:34.991
l agree with you entirely.

01:20:36.666 --> 01:20:40.796
My husband says
you don't care about the poor,

01:20:40.904 --> 01:20:44.271
so you can't really do
any good for our country.

01:20:47.076 --> 01:20:50.842
l don't believe you would hurt the poor.

01:20:51.347 --> 01:20:54.646
You'll try to persuade them.
That's all.

01:21:01.124 --> 01:21:03.058
But the problem is...

01:21:05.495 --> 01:21:07.929
persuasion doesn't always work.

01:21:09.966 --> 01:21:13.458
You need something more.
-- What do you need?

01:21:17.073 --> 01:21:20.236
-- Let's not talk about that.
-- l want to know.

01:21:21.611 --> 01:21:24.136
l don't want to talk
about mundane things with you.

01:21:24.247 --> 01:21:25.646
Why?

01:21:28.084 --> 01:21:31.281
l want no note of discord
in our relationship.

01:21:32.255 --> 01:21:34.815
But l'd be really happy to help.

01:21:36.526 --> 01:21:37.823
This is beyond you, queen bee.

01:21:38.928 --> 01:21:41.123
Haven't you seen me going beyond?

01:21:42.265 --> 01:21:46.725
l know how far you can go.
Even so, l'd rather not talk about it.

01:21:46.836 --> 01:21:48.565
lt's a personal request.

01:21:49.672 --> 01:21:54.871
Then there's no reason for me to stay.

01:21:55.645 --> 01:21:57.112
l'm leaving.

01:21:57.213 --> 01:22:01.115
Queen bee, please don't leave angry!

01:22:01.217 --> 01:22:05.711
lf l can't help you with Swadeshi,
then l'm just wasting my time here.

01:22:05.822 --> 01:22:08.290
l just didn't want you to worry about me.

01:22:08.925 --> 01:22:11.621
Must we only talk about politics?

01:22:11.728 --> 01:22:13.195
Only about my work?

01:22:13.796 --> 01:22:17.254
Promise me you'll tell me
if you need money,

01:22:17.367 --> 01:22:20.336
and you'll take it if l give it to you.

01:22:20.970 --> 01:22:22.494
l promise, queen bee.

01:22:23.139 --> 01:22:24.902
l promise.

01:22:25.174 --> 01:22:26.641
Queen bee?

01:22:27.310 --> 01:22:30.177
l'll come again this evening.
Please wait for me here.

01:22:30.647 --> 01:22:33.138
l hate having to send for you every time.

01:22:33.683 --> 01:22:35.275
Let go of me.

01:22:35.385 --> 01:22:39.446
Promise me you'll come to me every day.

01:22:40.423 --> 01:22:43.221
l must see you at least once a day.

01:22:44.494 --> 01:22:46.826
There's nothing wrong with that.

01:22:47.130 --> 01:22:49.462
Promise me.

01:22:49.565 --> 01:22:51.260
All right.

01:22:53.069 --> 01:22:57.165
Please let go of my hand.
l want to go.

01:23:20.963 --> 01:23:23.431
Khemi, clean the room later.

01:24:39.041 --> 01:24:44.673
<i>GentIy she waIks,</i>
<i>the beauteous one</i>

01:24:51.254 --> 01:24:53.313
Back so soon?

01:24:57.560 --> 01:24:59.323
What are you staring at?

01:25:01.531 --> 01:25:03.624
What is there to stare at but you?

01:25:04.734 --> 01:25:06.929
l've never seen anything like it.

01:25:08.204 --> 01:25:10.138
Such tender concern for our guest.

01:25:10.573 --> 01:25:12.939
He'll never want to leave.

01:25:14.677 --> 01:25:19.171
ln my day, we had to look
after our husbands too.

01:25:21.617 --> 01:25:25.678
lf only my brother--in--law
were a guest in his own house,

01:25:26.389 --> 01:25:28.220
he'd be warmly welcomed.

01:25:28.324 --> 01:25:31.293
l don't want any advice from you.

01:25:36.732 --> 01:25:39.895
l was just a small girl
when l came here as a bride.

01:25:40.670 --> 01:25:45.232
Your husband was
my playmate in those days.

01:25:47.143 --> 01:25:48.838
Where were you then?

01:25:48.945 --> 01:25:52.073
There's no need to repeat
what l already know.

01:25:57.086 --> 01:25:59.554
He was the only one
who understood my pain.

01:25:59.655 --> 01:26:01.213
He used to say,

01:26:01.924 --> 01:26:04.586
''We're still living in the Dark Ages.

01:26:05.261 --> 01:26:07.354
That's why you're suffering like this.

01:26:09.031 --> 01:26:13.058
For you, having a husband
is just as painful as losing one.''

01:26:13.569 --> 01:26:18.632
''My wife will be a free woman,'' he'd say.

01:26:21.844 --> 01:26:24.813
Well, now l see that free woman
before my very eyes.

01:26:29.085 --> 01:26:31.246
But don't forget,

01:26:32.255 --> 01:26:34.280
there's a God above us, dear sister.

01:26:34.824 --> 01:26:38.282
He can see you too.

01:26:51.607 --> 01:26:54.041
<i>I beIieved I had the strength to bear</i>

01:26:54.710 --> 01:26:59.807
<i>whatever misfortune</i>
<i>fate had in store for me.</i>

01:27:00.283 --> 01:27:05.812
<i>I wouId caII up visions of suffering</i>
<i>and steeI myseIf against them.</i>

01:27:06.589 --> 01:27:08.557
<i>Visions of poverty,</i>

01:27:08.658 --> 01:27:12.492
<i>dishonor or death.</i>

01:27:13.195 --> 01:27:16.722
<i>I even imagined BimaIa's death.</i>

01:27:17.900 --> 01:27:21.358
<i>But there was one thing</i>
<i>I couId never imagine happening.</i>

01:27:22.538 --> 01:27:26.497
<i>Now I keep asking myseIf</i>
<i>again and again.</i>

01:27:27.476 --> 01:27:29.637
<i>Do I have the strength to bear this?</i>

01:27:30.013 --> 01:27:34.279
-- Hail Motherland!
-- Hail Motherland!

01:27:54.371 --> 01:27:58.899
-- What do you want?
-- We have some questions.

01:27:59.009 --> 01:28:00.169
What are they?

01:28:00.277 --> 01:28:03.508
Why don't you ban
foreign goods in our market?

01:28:03.613 --> 01:28:06.776
-- l have my reasons.
-- ls it because you would lose money?

01:28:09.152 --> 01:28:13.384
l wouldn't, but the poor would.

01:28:13.757 --> 01:28:15.486
But our nation will profit.

01:28:15.592 --> 01:28:19.585
We buy domestic salt, sugar and clothing.

01:28:19.696 --> 01:28:21.391
How can you say that?

01:28:22.199 --> 01:28:24.827
How can you compare
yourselves with the poor?

01:28:25.302 --> 01:28:27.236
You have money.

01:28:27.337 --> 01:28:30.329
You can afford
to spend more on lndian goods.

01:28:31.875 --> 01:28:34.343
The poor aren't standing in your way.

01:28:35.011 --> 01:28:36.376
Why are you standing in theirs?

01:28:36.780 --> 01:28:39.749
You want to oppose an entire nation
that's taken the Swadeshi oath?

01:28:39.850 --> 01:28:40.646
Never.

01:28:41.685 --> 01:28:43.585
That's beyond my power.

01:28:44.287 --> 01:28:47.518
But how can you say
the entire nation has taken your oath?

01:28:48.325 --> 01:28:50.088
Look at the evidence.

01:28:50.193 --> 01:28:52.593
Aren't the traders part of this nation?

01:28:52.696 --> 01:28:55.961
So you won't ban foreign goods?

01:28:57.567 --> 01:28:58.966
No,

01:28:59.469 --> 01:29:02.302
because those goods don't belong to me.

01:29:02.405 --> 01:29:04.100
Hail Motherland!

01:29:25.996 --> 01:29:27.395
What are you looking for?

01:29:28.765 --> 01:29:30.494
<i>PassifIora.</i>

01:29:31.868 --> 01:29:33.802
Didn't you have a vial?

01:29:35.539 --> 01:29:37.473
Are you having trouble sleeping?

01:29:39.242 --> 01:29:42.678
One sleeps less as one grows older,

